Executive Profile
G. Ruffner Page Jr.President and Director, McWane, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. G. Ruffner Page Jr. has been the President of Mcwane, Inc. since 1999. Mr. Page joined Mcwane, Inc. in 1993 and served as its Executive Vice President from 1994 to 1998. Prior to McWane, he held management positions at National Bank of Commerce from 1989 to 1993, the Remington Fund from 1986 to 1989 and Bankers Trust Company in New York and Atlanta. He has been the Chairman of Community Foundation Of Greater Birmingham Inc. He has been a Director of National Commerce ... Corporation since 2010 and serves as its Lead Independent Director. He serves as a Director of Southern Research Institute, O'Neal Industries, First American Bank, National Bank of Commerce, O'Neal Steel Inc. and McWane Inc. Mr. Page serves as a Director of Protective Investment Company, a subsidiary of Protective Life Corporation. He served as a Director of Cormatrix Cardiovascular, Inc. since November 10, 2016 until March 9, 2017. He served as Director of Birmingham Airport Authority. He served as a Director of Alabama National Bancorporation since 1995. He is a member of the Downtown Rotary, Leadership Birmingham, Leadership Alabama and serves on the Boards of the Alabama Symphony, the Birmingham Museum of Art, the Community Foundation of Greater Birmingham, the Birmingham Education Foundation and the Emmet O'Neil Library Foundation Board, The Vulcan Park Foundation Board and the Altamont School Board. Mr. Page graduated from Vanderbilt University in Nashville, Tennessee in 1981 with a BA in Philosophy and Psychology with a minor in Economics. He is also a graduate of the University of Virginia, Darden School of Business in Charlottesville, Virginia in 1986 .Read Full Background




